      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GO JUDE (4) carved over from wide out and boxed on strongly to finish half a length away in second (22.83) behind Bear It Is at this track. Well-placed to take this out. HARTLAND BUDDY (1) was sent out at big odds from this same box last time but ran above himself when a 4 length second (22.37) at Ballarat in T3 Grade 6. This tougher but expected to be in the finish. MISS BARBIE (3) hit the ground running from the squeeze draw with a fast early split last time, but run over late and missed the frame when a 4 length sixth (23.01) over 390m at this track. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings five times from 10 starts. In the mix. WHIPSTICK JORDAN (6) is not to be discarded.",
